{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775851117696,"sessionID":"ses_28706999cffeGRH9hcQ8s0loip","part":{"id":"prt_d78f998fb001UPgbM0WEkM3he4","messageID":"msg_d78f99018001ytbjIblenvNhVY","sessionID":"ses_28706999cffeGRH9hcQ8s0loip","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_716fcd2ec2e54439a3ace34b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n6: \n7: ## Base Specifications\n8: \n9: - **AR**: AR-012\n10: - **Module**: `pkg/store`\n11: - **Language**: Go\n12: - **Size**: S\n13: - **Base Specs**: \n14:   - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n15:   - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n16:   - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n17: \n18: ---\n19: \n20: ## Background\n21: \n22: The agentcube system requires a session storage abstraction to persist sandbox metadata keyed by session id. The store module provides a unified interface over Redis and Valkey backends, with support for:\n23: - Session CRUD operations (create, read, update, delete)\n24: - Expiry-based and activity-based session listing for garbage collection\n25: - Index maintenance via sorted sets\n26: - Provider selection via environment variables\n27: - Singleton initialization pattern\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Requirement: Store Interface Contract\n32: \n33: ### Scenario: Store interface provides all required methods\n34: \n35: **GIVEN** a configured Redis or Valkey backend  \n36: **WHEN** the `Store` interface is used  \n37: **THEN** the following methods are available:\n38: - `Ping(ctx context.Context) error` — verifies connectivity\n39: - `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — retrieves sandbox by session id\n40: - `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — creates new sandbox record\n41: - `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandboxStore *types.SandboxInfo) error` — updates existing sandbox\n42: - `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error` — removes sandbox\n43: - `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists expired sessions\n44: - `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx context.Context, before time.Time, limit int64) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)` — lists inactive sessions\n45: - `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, at time.Time) error` — updates last activity timestamp\n46: - `Close() error` — closes the store connection\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: ## Requirement: Provider Selection\n51: \n52: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Redis provider\n53: \n54: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"redis\"` (case-insensitive)  \n55: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n56: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed using environment variables `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD`\n57: \n58: ### Scenario: STORE_TYPE selects Valkey provider\n59: \n60: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to `\"valkey\"` (case-insensitive)  \n61: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called for initialization  \n62: **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed using environment variables `VALKEY_ADDR` and `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n63: \n64: ### Scenario: Default provider is Redis when STORE_TYPE unset\n65: \n66: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set  \n67: **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes  \n68: **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed by default\n69: \n70: ### Scenario: Invalid STORE_TYPE fails initialization\n71: \n72: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is set to an unsupported value (e.g., `\"memcached\"`)  \n73: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n74: **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## Requirement: Redis Environment Configuration\n79: \n80: ### Scenario: Redis requires REDIS_ADDR\n81: \n82: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `redis` or unset  \n83: **WHEN** Redis store initializes without `REDIS_ADDR` environment variable  \n84: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating REDIS_ADDR is required\n85: \n86: ### Scenario: Redis password required by default\n87: \n88: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set and `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n89: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n90: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n91: \n92: ### Scenario: Redis password optional when explicitly disabled\n93: \n94: **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` is set  \n95: **AND** `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n96: **WHEN** `REDIS_PASSWORD` is empty  \n97: **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n98: \n99: ---\n100: \n101: ## Requirement: Valkey Environment Configuration\n102: \n103: ### Scenario: Valkey requires VALKEY_ADDR\n104: \n105: **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is `valkey`  \n106: **WHEN** Valkey store initializes without `VALKEY_ADDR` environment variable  \n107: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating VALKEY_ADDR is required\n108: \n109: ### Scenario: Valkey password required by default\n110: \n111: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set and `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is not `\"false\"`  \n112: **WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty or not set  \n113: **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password is required\n114: \n115: ### Scenario: Valkey password optional when explicitly disabled\n116: \n117: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR` is set  \n118: **AND** `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `\"false\"`  \n119: **WHEN** `VALKEY_PASSWORD` is empty  \n120: **THEN** initialization succeeds without password\n121: \n122: ### Scenario: Valkey DisableCache option from environment\n123: \n124: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n125: **WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n126: **THEN** `DisableCache` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n127: \n128: ### Scenario: Valkey ForceSingleClient option from environment\n129: \n130: **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` is set to `\"true\"`  \n131: **WHEN** Valkey client options are built  \n132: **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is set to `true` on `ClientOption`\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## Requirement: Session Key Naming\n137: \n138: ### Scenario: Session key uses prefix concatenation\n139: \n140: **GIVEN** a session id `abc-123`  \n141: **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data  \n142: **THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123` (prefix `\"session:\"` concatenated with session id)\n143: \n144: ---\n145: \n146: ## Requirement: Ping Connectivity Verification\n147: \n148: ### Scenario: Redis ping returns PONG\n149: \n150: **GIVEN** a healthy Redis server  \n151: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Redis store  \n152: **THEN** the implementation issues PING command  \n153: **AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n154: \n155: ### Scenario: Valkey ping returns PONG\n156: \n157: **GIVEN** a healthy Valkey server  \n158: **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called on Valkey store  \n159: **THEN** the implementation issues `B().Ping()`  \n160: **AND** expects string response `\"PONG\"`\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ## Requirement: Not Found Semantics\n165: \n166: ### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n167: \n168: **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend  \n169: **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID` runs with non-existent session id  \n170: **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` with message `\"store: not found\"`\n171: \n172: ### Scenario: Redis backend returns Nil for missing key\n173: \n174: **GIVEN** Redis store  \n175: **WHEN** GET command returns Redis `Nil`  \n176: **THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n177: \n178: ### Scenario: Valkey backend returns nil for missing key\n179: \n180: **GIVEN** Valkey store  \n181: **WHEN** GET command returns `IsValkeyNil` true  \n182: **THEN** `ErrNotFound` is returned\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## Requirement: StoreSandbox Validation\n187: \n188: ### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n189: \n190: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)` is called  \n191: **WHEN** the method executes  \n192: **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil\n193: \n194: ### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n195: \n196: **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox` is called with sandbox where `ExpiresAt` is zero time  \n197: **WHEN** the method validates input  \n198: **THEN** error indicates invalid expiry\n199: \n200: ---\n201: \n202: ## Requirement: StoreSandbox Atomicity\n203: \n204: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox creates session with all indexes\n205: \n206: **GIVEN** a valid `SandboxInfo` with `SessionID`, `ExpiresAt`, and other fields  \n207: **WHEN** `StoreSandbox` is called  \n208: **THEN** the operation executes atomically:\n209: - Session key (`session:{id}`) is set with JSON value using SETNX\n210: - `session:expiry` ZSET gets member with score = `ExpiresAt.Unix()`\n211: - `session:last_activity` ZSET gets member with score = `time.Now().Unix()`\n212: \n213: ### Scenario: StoreSandbox fails on any pipeline error\n214: \n215: **GIVEN** Redis/Valkey pipeline/multi operation  \n216: **WHEN** any command in the batch fails  \n217: **THEN** the operation returns error and no partial state is left\n218: \n219: ---\n220: \n221: ## Requirement: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n222: \n223: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox only modifies session value\n224: \n225: **GIVEN** an existing session with key `session:{id}`  \n226: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called with new sandbox data  \n227: **THEN** only the session JSON value is updated using SET with XX flag  \n228: **AND** expiry and last-activity ZSET entries are NOT modified\n229: \n230: ### Scenario: UpdateSandbox fails on missing key\n231: \n232: **GIVEN** no session key exists for the given session id  \n233: **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox` is called  \n234: **THEN** error is returned indicating key does not exist (Redis: SETXX returns false; Valkey: response not \"OK\")\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Requirement: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n239: \n240: ### Scenario: Delete removes session key and both indexes\n241: \n242: **GIVEN** an existing session with data in all three keys  \n243: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` is called  \n244: **THEN** the operation removes:\n245: - Session key (`session:{id}`) via DEL\n246: - Member from `session:expiry` ZSET via ZREM\n247: - Member from `session:last_activity` ZSET via ZREM\n248: \n249: ### Scenario: Delete executes atomically\n250: \n251: **GIVEN** a valid session id  \n252: **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` runs  \n253: **THEN** all delete operations execute in one pipeline/multi block\n254: \n255: ---\n256: \n257: ## Requirement: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n258: \n259: ### Scenario: ListExpired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on expiry index\n260: \n261: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n262: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n263: **THEN** it selects members from `session:expiry` with scores from negative infinity to `before.Unix()`  \n264: **AND** limited to `limit` entries\n265: \n266: ### Scenario: ListExpired with limit <= 0 returns nil\n267: \n268: **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n269: **WHEN** executed  \n270: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n271: \n272: ### Scenario: ListExpired loads JSON for each session id\n273: \n274: **GIVEN** ZRANGEBYSCORE returns session ids  \n275: **WHEN** fetching sandbox data  \n276: **THEN** each id is used to GET the corresponding `session:{id}` key  \n277: **AND** JSON is unmarshaled to `SandboxInfo`\n278: \n279: ---\n280: \n281: ## Requirement: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n282: \n283: ### Scenario: ListInactive uses ZRANGEBYSCORE on last_activity index\n284: \n285: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0  \n286: **WHEN** the implementation queries the index  \n287: **THEN** it selects members from `session:last_activity` with scores ≤ `before.Unix()`  \n288: **AND** limited to `limit` entries\n289: \n290: ### Scenario: ListInactive with limit <= 0 returns nil\n291: \n292: **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes` called with limit <= 0  \n293: **WHEN** executed  \n294: **THEN** returns `nil, nil`\n295: \n296: ---\n297: \n298: ## Requirement: List Operations Tolerate Missing Keys\n299: \n300: ### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member is skipped\n301: \n302: **GIVEN** a session id returned from ZSET but without corresponding string value  \n303: **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` runs  \n304: **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice  \n305: **AND** the operation does not fail for the whole batch\n306: \n307: ---\n308: \n309: ## Requirement: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n310: \n311: ### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n312: \n313: **GIVEN** empty session id  \n314: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n315: **THEN** error is returned\n316: \n317: ### Scenario: Zero time uses current time\n318: \n319: **GIVEN** an existing session  \n320: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with zero time  \n321: **THEN** `time.Now()` is used as the activity timestamp\n322: \n323: ### Scenario: Non-zero time uses provided value\n324: \n325: **GIVEN** an existing session  \n326: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called with non-zero `at` timestamp  \n327: **THEN** the provided timestamp is used as the activity score in ZADD\n328: \n329: ### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity requires existing session\n330: \n331: **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key exists  \n332: **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity` is called  \n333: **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ## Requirement: Singleton Initialization\n338: \n339: ### Scenario: Storage returns singleton instance\n340: \n341: **GIVEN** `Storage()` is called multiple times  \n342: **WHEN** after first initialization  \n343: **THEN** the same store instance is returned every time\n344: \n345: ### Scenario: Concurrent Storage calls initialize once\n346: \n347: **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently  \n348: **WHEN** they execute concurrently  \n349: **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once via `sync.Once`\n350: \n351: ### Scenario: Init failure triggers fatal log\n352: \n353: **GIVEN** store initialization fails  \n354: **WHEN** `Storage()` is called  \n355: **THEN** `klog.Fatalf` is called with error message\n356: \n357: ---\n358: \n359: ## Requirement: Redis and Valkey Equivalence\n360: \n361: ### Scenario: Both backends implement same interface\n362: \n363: **GIVEN** Redis and Valkey stores with equivalent configuration  \n364: **WHEN** equivalent operations are performed  \n365: **THEN** both backends produce identical results for:\n366: - Session CRUD operations\n367: - Listing expired/inactive sessions\n368: - Last activity updates\n369: - Error semantics (`ErrNotFound`)\n370: \n371: ---\n372: \n373: ## Acceptance Criteria\n374: \n375: - [ ] Store interface defined in `pkg/store/store.go`\n376: - [ ] ErrNotFound error defined and returned for missing sessions\n377: - [ ] Redis implementation in `pkg/store/store_redis.go`\n378: - [ ] Valkey implementation in `pkg/store/store_valkey.go`\n379: - [ ] Singleton pattern in `pkg/store/singleton.go` with `Storage()` function\n380: - [ ] Environment variables parsed correctly for both providers\n381: - [ ] Password policy enforced (required by default, optional when disabled)\n382: - [ ] Session key naming uses `session:` prefix\n383: - [ ] Expiry index maintained via `session:expiry` ZSET\n384: - [ ] Last activity index maintained via `session:last_activity` ZSET\n385: - [ ] Atomic operations for Store, Update, Delete\n386: - [ ] List operations with limit <= 0 return nil\n387: - [ ] Orphan ZSET members handled gracefully\n388: - [ ] All acceptance scenarios pass verification\n389: \n390: ---\n391: \n392: ## References\n393: \n394: - Delta Spec: `changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md`\n395: - Base Spec: `deployment/client-go.md`\n396: - Base Spec: `session-store/design.md`\n397: - Base Spec: `session-store/spec.md`\n\n(End of file - total 397 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-012 — 会话存储接口定义\n\n## Overview\n\nThis delta-spec defines acceptance scenarios for implementing session storage interface in `pkg/store`.\n\n## Base Specifications\n\n- **AR**: AR-012\n- **Module**: `pkg/store`\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: S\n- **Base Specs**: \n  - `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client for runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh API\n  - `session-store/design.md` — Session store design with Store interface\n  - `session-store/spec.md` — Session store specification with requirements\n\n---\n\n## Background","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/changes/AR-012/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775851117677,"end":1775851117693}}}}
